Job Description:
Responsibilities:
Manage the establishment of trade department, formulate work plans and relevant budget, take full charge of daily management of the department;
Manage import and export business process;
Handle contracts, letter of credit and shipping documents independently
Collect and analyze important industrial data, explore domestic and foreign markets actively and effectively;
Sign, manage and execute bulk commodity trading contracts, as well as deal with relevant business matters;
Participate in business development and negotiations, including daily communication with important clients;
Manage internal documentation as well as assessment, training, rewards and remedy of personnel within the department;
Other tasks assigned by the management
Requirements:
BA/BS in the field of international trade, international finance and other related discipline;
5+ years’ experience executing management of import and export business, preferably experience in foreign companies of related fields;
Familiar with international settlement, as well as the business process, laws and regulations of import and export, professional knowledge of trade management and related skills;
Excellent team leadership and coordination skills, strong communication & negotiation skills;
Initiative, professional appearance, occupation ethics, moral, strong marketing capability;
Work well independently and able to adapt to environment.
